JOHANNESBURG - A policeman and five others suspects have been arrested in connection with the Glebelands Hostel murders.  (Photo: SAPS) Provincial Organised Crime investigators and several specialised police units raided the Harding and Glebelands Hostels in KZN on Wednesday. READ:Â Commission hears that Glebelands hitmen operate throughout KZN More than eighty people have been killed at Glebelands since 2014. During the raids, officers seized police gear and a state-issued laptop. The suspects will appear in court soon. eNCA